CLB-Server
==========

Build
-----

'clb-server' depends on 'dconvert'(api), another project under
Duckling.

Do 'mvn package' and get 'clb.war'.

Setup
-----

1) Get clbconfig.properties from its TEMPLATE and edit it.

2) With mysql, create the database, and tables by
WEB-INF/conf/clb_schema-xxx.sql.

3) Install mongodb-server (e.g. apt-get).

4) Build and install nginx-gridfs (in another directory).

5) Install redis (e.g. download and make).

6) 'dconvert-server' is optional. 'wopi' too.

7) Config tomcat for clb-server.

8) Run and enjoy.